          textEn: [
            "Song on Ascending Youzhou Tower \u2014 Chen Zi\u2019ang\nBefore me, I see no ancients; behind me, no followers. Contemplating the vastness of heaven and earth, alone I weep in sorrow!",
            "Gazing at Mount Tai \u2014 Du Fu\nWhat is Mount Tai like? Its green spans Qi and Lu endlessly. Nature gathers here all beauty; its slopes divide dusk from dawn. Swelling clouds cleanse the breast; straining eyes follow homing birds. Someday I shall reach the summit, and behold all mountains small.",
            "Ascending Feilai Peak \u2014 Wang Anshi\nAtop Feilai Mountain a thousand-ren tower; they say at cockcrow one sees the sun rise. I fear not clouds that block my view, for I stand at the very highest level.",
            "Touring Shanxi Village \u2014 Lu You\nDon\u2019t laugh at the farmer\u2019s murky rice wine; in harvest years, guests feast on ample fowl. Where mountains and waters seem to leave no path, past willows dark and flowers bright, another village appears.",
            "Miscellaneous Poems of Jihai (No. 5) \u2014 Gong Zizhen\nBoundless sorrow as the white sun sets; my riding whip points east toward the horizon. Fallen petals are not heartless things\u2014they turn to spring mud to nurture flowers anew."
          ],
